view.name: 500 Cities: City-level Data (GIS Friendly Format)
view.attribution: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, National Center for Chronic Disease Prevention and Health Promotion, Division of Population Health
view.description: 2013, 2014. Data were provided by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Division of Population Health, Epidemiology and Surveillance Branch. The project was funded by the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation (RWJF) in conjunction with the CDC Foundation. 500 cities project city-level data in GIS-friendly format. This dataset can be joined with city-level spatial data in a geographic information system (GIS) to produce maps of 27 measures at the city-level.
